Operating system :An Operating System performs all the basic tasks like managing file,process, and memory. Thus operating system acts as
manager of all the resources, i.e. resource manager. Thus operating system becomes an interface between user and machine
Os performs the following tasks:
	Process scheduling
	Memory management
	File Processing
	IO management
Different types of operating systems:
1) Batch operating system
2) Time sharing Operating system
3) Distributed Operating system
4) Network operating system
5) Real Time Operating system

Linux:
	Portable
	Multitasking
	MultiUser
	Virtual Memory
	GUI
	Hierarchical File System
Windows:
	kernel
	file system 
	memory manager
	Security management
